fraction(x) returns the fractional part of the model representation of x.
x = fraction(x) * radix(x)**exponent(x), except when x is zero.

default real examples:
x = -8  fraction(x) = -0.5  exponent(x) = 4
x = -3.5  fraction(x) = -0.875  exponent(x) = 2
x = -1  fraction(x) = -0.5  exponent(x) = 1
x = 0  fraction(x) = 0  exponent(x) = 0
x = 1  fraction(x) = 0.5  exponent(x) = 1
x = 3.5  fraction(x) = 0.875  exponent(x) = 2
x = 8  fraction(x) = 0.5  exponent(x) = 4

reconstruct nonzero values:
x = -8  reconstructed = -8
x = -3.5  reconstructed = -3.5
x = -1  reconstructed = -1
x = 1  reconstructed = 1
x = 3.5  reconstructed = 3.5
x = 8  reconstructed = 8

real kind examples:
fraction(3.5_4) = 0.875
fraction(3.5_8) = 0.875
